OnShape CAD Modelling
Assigned to design a private reading space on OnShape CAD Modelling tool which would accommodate one person and placed indoors for student to work. No extra lightings were included within the pod while maintaining privacy.
Tool and Techniques
Write something here.
Design Process:
Started with 3 different shapes to explore overall design and finalized triangle as primary shape and sphere to add imbalance. Explored rounded corners at entrance for visual continuity. With a final design on ready on Procreate, designed the space on OnShape CAD software and made a physical model using cardboard.
Challenges and design solutions:
1. Using triangle created a lot of visual distraction and uneasiness.
Solution: Added more rounded form in the design.
2. Required to add a desk in a restricted place for the user to keep stuff.
Solution: Designed a portable table to alter space as per user requirement.
Learning Outcomes
1. Learning the isometric sketching method.
2. First experience with CAD Modelling technique.
